                                        "},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Firstly notice that 2013/1001 and 20132013/1001 both leave a remainder other than zero. Secondly notice that 201320132013/1001 leaves a remainder of zero. Furthermore it is clear that every concatenation that is a multiple of 3 (e.g. 3,6,9...) divided by 1001 leaves a remainder of 0. Proceed to notice that 2013 is divisible by 3  (if the sum of the digits is divisible by 3, so is the number itself). Therefore the 2013th concatenation is a multiple 3, hence leaves a remainder of 0."}]},{"type":"text","text":"



                            "}]}

{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"text","text":"




                                        "},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that 201320132013/1001 is an integer. Therefore N=201320132013*(1+10^12+10^24+...+10^8048) is divisible by 1001."}]},{"type":"text","text":"



                            "}]}

{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"text","text":"




                                        "},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"First of all note that the number "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"201320132013"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":" is divisible by "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"1001"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":". Then, we have "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"N = 201320132013 \times 10^{0 \times 12} + 201320132013 \times 10^{1 \times 12} + \cdots + 201320132013 \times 10^{671 \times 12} "}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":", which is obviously contain factors of "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"201320132013"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":" and thus, can be divided by "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"1001"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":". Hence, the remainder is "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"0"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}}]},{"type":"text","text":"



                            "}]}

{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"text","text":"




                                        "},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Notice that "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"1001|201320132013"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"3|2013"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":", so "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"N\equiv\boxed{0}\pmod{1001}"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"text","text":"



                            "}]}

{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"text","text":"




                                        "},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"For 2013 concatenated 3 times and divided by 1001, 201320132013/1001=2111913 Since 2013 is divisible by 3, 2013/3=671 N will be 201320132013 concatenated 671 times Thus N/1001=2111913 concatenated 671 times So there will be no remainder and the answer is 0."}]},{"type":"text","text":"



                            "}]}

{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"text","text":"




                                        "},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"When 2013 is concatenated 3 times, the resulting number, 201320132013, is divisible by 1001. Thus, for every 3n, multiple of 3, concatenation, the resulting integer is a multiple of 1001. Since 2013 is a multiple of 3, 2013 concatenated 2013 times is a multiple of 1001. Thus the remainder is 0"}]},{"type":"text","text":"



                            "}]}

